      "message": "This should be fConfig, right?\n\nRight now fConfig is a non-allocated class member var, but ideally should probably be more like Compiler where we make_unique\u003cProgramConfig\u003e at the start of compilation and then move it into the Program when compilation succeeds. Alternatively, we can probably just copy fConfig here via `std::make_unique\u003cProgramConfig\u003e(fConfig)`.",
